1
00:00:02,586 --> 00:00:04,585
The rhythm of the wind sharpens the skill of deduction.

2
00:00:04,586 --> 00:00:06,685
Black entanglement also unravels.

3
00:00:06,686 --> 00:00:08,485
The conspiracy of the Black Organization is about to be confirmed.

4
00:00:08,486 --> 00:00:10,985
The truth becomes clearer after one incident and another.

5
00:00:10,986 --> 00:00:12,585
He sees through the one and only truth.

6
00:00:12,586 --> 00:00:14,485
A child in appearance with the I.Q. of an adult.

7
00:00:14,486 --> 00:00:16,286
His name is Detective Conan!

8
00:01:55,365 --> 00:01:58,064
Dr. Agasa and I got a hint of coming in contact with

9
00:01:58,065 --> 00:02:00,864
the Black Organization from the diary of Mr. Itakura who had been killed.

10
00:02:00,865 --> 00:02:04,765
Therefore, we came over to Mr. Itakura's villa.

11
00:02:05,765 --> 00:02:07,265
Then...

12
00:02:14,065 --> 00:02:15,565
Hey, what's going on?

13
00:02:17,765 --> 00:02:18,865
Vodka?

14
00:02:19,865 --> 00:02:21,564
You're there, aren't you?

15
00:02:21,565 --> 00:02:23,264
They've found out.

16
00:02:23,265 --> 00:02:26,664
They've found out that we failed to open the e-mail.

17
00:02:26,665 --> 00:02:27,764
Yes.

18
00:02:27,765 --> 00:02:30,864
Hey, answer me.

19
00:02:30,865 --> 00:02:34,164
I know you're at that villa.

20
00:02:34,165 --> 00:02:35,765
Shinichi?

21
00:02:36,765 --> 00:02:39,164
Hurry up and answer me,

22
00:02:39,165 --> 00:02:40,565
Mr. Itakura.

23
00:02:41,565 --> 00:02:42,565
Hey!

24
00:02:47,365 --> 00:02:53,065
"Contact with the Black Organization (Pursuit Edition)"

25
00:02:55,365 --> 00:02:57,764
Hey, answer me.

26
00:02:57,765 --> 00:03:01,064
I know you're at that villa.

27
00:03:01,065 --> 00:03:02,964
Hurry up and answer me,

28
00:03:02,965 --> 00:03:04,765
Mr. Itakura.

29
00:03:06,765 --> 00:03:09,364
I guess we've no choice

30
00:03:09,365 --> 00:03:11,264
but to make it out the back door

31
00:03:11,265 --> 00:03:13,565
and hide in the blizzard.

32
00:03:16,165 --> 00:03:18,564
Oh, sorry. It's so dark in here

33
00:03:18,565 --> 00:03:20,365
that I was having trouble picking up the phone.

34
00:03:22,665 --> 00:03:24,864
It seems that the electrical circuit went out

35
00:03:24,865 --> 00:03:26,564
because of this blizzard,

36
00:03:26,565 --> 00:03:30,464
I couldn't open the mail because of this, too.

37
00:03:30,465 --> 00:03:32,264
That's what you get for trying to receive mail

38
00:03:32,265 --> 00:03:34,464
in a mountain villa like that.

39
00:03:34,465 --> 00:03:36,064
Hey, wait a minute.

40
00:03:36,065 --> 00:03:40,164
How come your answer phone's working despite the blackout?

41
00:03:40,165 --> 00:03:44,464
Well, blackouts are frequent in this area because it snows a lot.

42
00:03:44,465 --> 00:03:48,065
That's why I'm using a phone equipped with a built-in battery.

43
00:03:50,065 --> 00:03:51,365
I see.

44
00:03:53,465 --> 00:03:57,665
It's amazing how you found out I was here.

45
00:04:00,065 --> 00:04:03,965
"Please turn on the light" -We know all about you.

46
00:04:05,265 --> 00:04:08,964
Don't tell me you were keeping watch over this villa, were you?

47
00:04:08,965 --> 00:04:11,664
We weren't, don't worry.

48
00:04:11,665 --> 00:04:13,064
Just as promised,

49
00:04:13,065 --> 00:04:15,864
we're nowhere near you.

50
00:04:15,865 --> 00:04:20,664
You're finished with that system software in question, I hope.

51
00:04:20,665 --> 00:04:22,665
Yes, somehow.

52
00:04:24,165 --> 00:04:26,064
Is there anyone with you?

53
00:04:26,065 --> 00:04:27,564
Hey, answer me!

54
00:04:27,565 --> 00:04:29,464
What is that sound just now?

55
00:04:29,465 --> 00:04:31,364
Sound?

56
00:04:31,365 --> 00:04:33,664
It's the wind.

57
00:04:33,665 --> 00:04:36,165
The sound of the wind tapping on the window.

58
00:04:37,165 --> 00:04:39,764
That's right, it's snowing heavily over there, too.

59
00:04:39,765 --> 00:04:43,064
So, I can't use the computer.

60
00:04:43,065 --> 00:04:46,164
I hate to say this, but would you give me the info directly?

61
00:04:46,165 --> 00:04:49,165
The time and place of where I should hand this software over to you.

62
00:04:50,265 --> 00:04:52,164
All right, fine.

63
00:04:52,165 --> 00:04:55,264
I'll say it just once, so listen well.

64
00:04:55,265 --> 00:04:58,964
You know the station that's under construction called "Kenbashi"?

65
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:02,664
The fashionable station that's going to be added to the Toto Subway Line.

66
00:05:02,665 --> 00:05:04,764
Tomorrow morning at midnight,

67
00:05:04,765 --> 00:05:06,664
come and wait in front of coin locker number 0032

68
00:05:06,665 --> 00:05:10,164
located on the basement floor of the station.

69
00:05:10,165 --> 00:05:14,165
Don't forget to bring the system software, got that?

70
00:05:15,165 --> 00:05:18,064
No. Tomorrow's a bad day.

71
00:05:18,065 --> 00:05:19,664
What?

72
00:05:19,665 --> 00:05:23,564
I'm going to have to be hospitalized from this evening for a health check.

73
00:05:23,565 --> 00:05:25,064
You know about it, don't you?

74
00:05:25,065 --> 00:05:27,764
About my bad heart condition.

75
00:05:27,765 --> 00:05:31,464
Don't tell me that you're trying to buy time

76
00:05:31,465 --> 00:05:34,264
because you still haven't completed that software?

77
00:05:34,265 --> 00:05:36,364
No, of course not.

78
00:05:36,365 --> 00:05:38,764
The software is complete.

79
00:05:38,765 --> 00:05:40,764
Then, when is it convenient for you?

80
00:05:40,765 --> 00:05:42,364
After I'm discharged from the hospital,

81
00:05:42,365 --> 00:05:43,964
so about three to four days later.

82
00:05:43,965 --> 00:05:46,664
No, give me five days.

83
00:05:46,665 --> 00:05:50,064
Nonsense. We can't wait that long.

84
00:05:50,065 --> 00:05:51,964
Postpone your hospitalization appointment.

85
00:05:51,965 --> 00:05:55,564
I finally got an appointment with a famous heart surgeon,

86
00:05:55,565 --> 00:05:57,564
so I can't change the date.

87
00:05:57,565 --> 00:05:59,264
If I were to hand it over to you before I enter the hospital,

88
00:05:59,265 --> 00:06:04,064
it has to be today, but the construction workers will be there at daybreak.

89
00:06:04,065 --> 00:06:07,764
It's not convenient for you guys then, isn't it?

90
00:06:07,765 --> 00:06:09,564
At 4 am, then.

91
00:06:09,565 --> 00:06:12,664
Four hours from now at 4 am.

92
00:06:12,665 --> 00:06:14,964
Bring the software to the place I told you.

93
00:06:14,965 --> 00:06:17,064
Four hours from now?

94
00:06:17,065 --> 00:06:19,564
From Gunma to Tokyo?

95
00:06:19,565 --> 00:06:20,764
What's the problem?

96
00:06:20,765 --> 00:06:21,765
If it's completed,

97
00:06:21,766 --> 00:06:24,164
you should be able to bring it with you, shouldn't you?

98
00:06:24,165 --> 00:06:25,764
Okay.

99
00:06:25,765 --> 00:06:28,565
Four hours from now, I'll take it there.

100
00:06:29,565 --> 00:06:32,964
But don't ambush me.

101
00:06:32,965 --> 00:06:37,464
If I spot any of your people, this entire deal is off.

102
00:06:37,465 --> 00:06:40,064
Even if you were to force this software away from me,

103
00:06:40,065 --> 00:06:41,464
keep in mind that doing so may throw the method

104
00:06:41,465 --> 00:06:44,765
of using this software into the pits of darkness forever.

105
00:06:45,765 --> 00:06:49,764
You're sure a cautious fellow, just like rumor has it.

106
00:06:49,765 --> 00:06:51,464
Okay. Four hours from now,

107
00:06:51,465 --> 00:06:53,364
in front of locker number 0032

108
00:06:53,365 --> 00:06:55,764
at the basement of Kenbashi Station.

109
00:06:55,765 --> 00:06:58,765
-Don't be late. -Yes.

110
00:07:02,265 --> 00:07:04,964
All right, I got them.

111
00:07:04,965 --> 00:07:06,764
Hey, just what do you intend to do?

112
00:07:06,765 --> 00:07:08,864
Don't tell me that you're going to listen to them

113
00:07:08,865 --> 00:07:11,664
and take that software over?

114
00:07:11,665 --> 00:07:13,964
I'm not listening to them.

115
00:07:13,965 --> 00:07:16,764
I lead the conversation so that the handover time of the software

116
00:07:16,765 --> 00:07:19,164
would be rushed to 4 this morning,

117
00:07:19,165 --> 00:07:21,464
by sounding flustered.

118
00:07:21,465 --> 00:07:23,564
What?

119
00:07:23,565 --> 00:07:26,764
The news of Mr. Itakura's death

120
00:07:26,765 --> 00:07:28,764
may be aired when morning comes, right?

121
00:07:28,765 --> 00:07:30,664
If they find out,

122
00:07:30,665 --> 00:07:33,864
this deal as well as clues about them will go down the drain.

123
00:07:33,865 --> 00:07:35,664
Now, the jewelry robber who is at large...

124
00:07:35,665 --> 00:07:37,164
Fortunately, it seems

125
00:07:37,165 --> 00:07:39,864
that none of the news stations are covering news about his case yet.

126
00:07:39,865 --> 00:07:42,664
Which means this is what you intended to do, to begin with?

127
00:07:42,665 --> 00:07:45,964
Yes, I was planning to tell them

128
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:48,264
to rush the hand over time to an earlier time

129
00:07:48,265 --> 00:07:50,564
when I receive the e-mail from them.

130
00:07:50,565 --> 00:07:54,864
So, let's erase all traces of us having been here

131
00:07:54,865 --> 00:07:57,964
and get out of here with your beetle.

132
00:07:57,965 --> 00:07:59,864
Out of here?

133
00:07:59,865 --> 00:08:04,264
They may be watching us from somewhere around this villa, right?

134
00:08:04,265 --> 00:08:06,864
If we carelessly go out just like that to the car that's parked outside,

135
00:08:06,865 --> 00:08:09,964
they may spot us.

136
00:08:09,965 --> 00:08:11,664
Don't worry.

137
00:08:11,665 --> 00:08:15,064
If Vodka or any of his people were around,

138
00:08:15,065 --> 00:08:16,764
they would've easily seen through my lie

139
00:08:16,765 --> 00:08:18,064
that I couldn't use the computer

140
00:08:18,065 --> 00:08:20,664
because the circuit was cut off by the blizzard.

141
00:08:20,665 --> 00:08:22,564
I see.

142
00:08:22,565 --> 00:08:25,664
That's why you asked me to turn on the lights to this villa?

143
00:08:25,665 --> 00:08:26,864
Yes.

144
00:08:26,865 --> 00:08:30,164
We know at the least that none of his people is at a distance

145
00:08:30,165 --> 00:08:33,564
where they can see the lights of the villa.

146
00:08:33,565 --> 00:08:36,264
They probably tracked this place,

147
00:08:36,265 --> 00:08:39,064
using some alarm system that would warn them

148
00:08:39,065 --> 00:08:41,164
and specify the computer of the one they're sending the mail to,

149
00:08:41,165 --> 00:08:42,864
just in case the mail that they sent

150
00:08:42,865 --> 00:08:45,364
isn't opened by the receiver of the mail.

151
00:08:45,365 --> 00:08:48,564
Either way, part of the members of the group will be arrested.

152
00:08:48,565 --> 00:08:51,064
I'll confirm the contents of this software

153
00:08:51,065 --> 00:08:53,964
with the laptop computer in the beetle,

154
00:08:53,965 --> 00:08:56,364
and if it's some outrageous software

155
00:08:56,365 --> 00:08:58,964
that could be used for a hideous crime or something.

156
00:08:58,965 --> 00:09:00,664
You're going to report it to the police,

157
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:02,564
and specify the place of the deal,

158
00:09:02,565 --> 00:09:07,264
so they can ambush the culprits and arrest whoever shows up, right?

159
00:09:07,265 --> 00:09:08,665
Yes.

160
00:09:11,665 --> 00:09:13,664
Darn. No good.

161
00:09:13,665 --> 00:09:17,064
We need to enter a password for this software, too.

162
00:09:17,065 --> 00:09:18,464
Just like the e-mail,

163
00:09:18,465 --> 00:09:22,964
a password is been set between Mr. Itakura and those guys.

164
00:09:22,965 --> 00:09:25,564
Then, just make a copy of it for now.

165
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:27,064
I can't do that either.

166
00:09:27,065 --> 00:09:30,264
It's protected with a copy guard.

167
00:09:30,265 --> 00:09:33,064
Under this condition, the police won't move.

168
00:09:33,065 --> 00:09:37,364
Aren't they always secretly armed with guns?

169
00:09:37,365 --> 00:09:40,064
If you report that there will be a deal involving guns,

170
00:09:40,065 --> 00:09:42,364
maybe at least two or three officers will come.

171
00:09:42,365 --> 00:09:45,564
We don't even know how many those guys have on their side.

172
00:09:45,565 --> 00:09:46,764
So, with only a small number on our side,

173
00:09:46,765 --> 00:09:49,264
we're more likely to be biting off our heads.

174
00:09:49,265 --> 00:09:51,364
Unless we find out what their purpose is,

175
00:09:51,365 --> 00:09:53,864
and present evidence to the police as to how dangerous they are,

176
00:09:53,865 --> 00:09:55,664
as well as how large their organization is,

177
00:09:55,665 --> 00:09:58,564
and have the police come equipped with sufficient men,

178
00:09:58,565 --> 00:10:00,265
it'll be difficult to lay our hands on them.

179
00:10:02,265 --> 00:10:04,264
How frustrating.

180
00:10:04,265 --> 00:10:05,964
We know that they're coming

181
00:10:05,965 --> 00:10:07,664
and yet we can't do a thing about it.

182
00:10:07,665 --> 00:10:10,265
Not really. There's still one way.

183
00:10:11,565 --> 00:10:14,264
It's a bit dangerous, though.

184
00:10:14,265 --> 00:10:17,665
Hey, don't tell me that you're planning to meet them directly?

185
00:10:19,065 --> 00:10:21,064
Hey, Dr. Agasa.

186
00:10:21,065 --> 00:10:22,664
Don't tell me that...

187
00:10:22,665 --> 00:10:24,465
Yes, you're most probably right.

188
00:10:27,965 --> 00:10:30,264
It's a flat after all.

189
00:10:30,265 --> 00:10:33,164
We've got to call a nearby service station

190
00:10:33,165 --> 00:10:36,364
and have them bring us over a spare tire.

191
00:10:36,365 --> 00:10:37,964
Is it going to work?

192
00:10:37,965 --> 00:10:39,664
I don't think there's any service station

193
00:10:39,665 --> 00:10:41,665
that'll come at this time of night.

194
00:10:42,665 --> 00:10:45,364
Well, we may as well relax and wait in the car then.

195
00:10:45,365 --> 00:10:49,364
We won't make it in time for meeting those guys if we do that!

196
00:10:49,365 --> 00:10:51,564
I'm sure that this is God's way of telling you

197
00:10:51,565 --> 00:10:54,365
to keep from taking dangerous action, Shinichi.

198
00:10:55,665 --> 00:10:57,665
Darn.

199
00:11:00,465 --> 00:11:02,365
A car?

200
00:11:03,365 --> 00:11:06,565
Hey!

201
00:11:10,465 --> 00:11:12,064
What's up?

202
00:11:12,065 --> 00:11:15,864
Oh, well. We got a flat.

203
00:11:15,865 --> 00:11:18,464
We want to go back to Tokyo,

204
00:11:18,465 --> 00:11:20,264
but won't you give us a lift?

205
00:11:20,265 --> 00:11:21,764
Tokyo?

206
00:11:21,765 --> 00:11:24,064
What do you say?

207
00:11:24,065 --> 00:11:27,264
Why not? We're going in that direction anyway.

208
00:11:27,265 --> 00:11:29,964
Gramps, are you familiar with the roads around here?

209
00:11:29,965 --> 00:11:31,764
Well, yes, sort of.

210
00:11:31,765 --> 00:11:33,564
Okay, you get in the front seat, gramps.

211
00:11:33,565 --> 00:11:35,364
And the kid in the backseat.

212
00:11:35,365 --> 00:11:37,165
Thanks.

213
00:11:44,265 --> 00:11:47,364
I'm sorry to intrude on you when you were sleeping, miss.

214
00:11:47,365 --> 00:11:51,165
It's okay, I was just kind of dozing.

215
00:11:59,065 --> 00:12:03,464
Cool! This is a foreign car, isn't it?

216
00:12:03,465 --> 00:12:05,864
Is this car yours, sir?

217
00:12:05,865 --> 00:12:08,064
Yes, I've gotten tired of it

218
00:12:08,065 --> 00:12:11,064
and was just thinking of getting myself another car, though.

219
00:12:11,065 --> 00:12:13,964
You must be rich,

220
00:12:13,965 --> 00:12:16,364
because this car is really expensive.

221
00:12:16,365 --> 00:12:17,764
Sort of.

222
00:12:17,765 --> 00:12:19,264
Although he may not look it,

223
00:12:19,265 --> 00:12:21,665
he's the heir to a big company, you know.

224
00:12:27,365 --> 00:12:28,765
Goodness!

225
00:12:35,065 --> 00:12:37,064
That sure was close.

226
00:12:37,065 --> 00:12:39,564
Snowy roads are dangerous after all.

227
00:12:39,565 --> 00:12:42,665
Well, let's not rush and drive safely.

228
00:12:45,665 --> 00:12:49,364
Hey, didn't you hear something funny just now?

229
00:12:49,365 --> 00:12:52,764
Really? I didn't hear anything.

230
00:12:52,765 --> 00:12:56,264
The stuff that we have in the trunk probably moved.

231
00:12:56,265 --> 00:12:58,464
It's nothing to sweat about.

232
00:12:58,465 --> 00:13:00,964
Hey, don't smoke!

233
00:13:00,965 --> 00:13:04,564
Did you forget that I hate cigarettes?

234
00:13:04,565 --> 00:13:08,264
Oh, sorry. That's right.

235
00:13:08,265 --> 00:13:11,764
Oh, to go to Tokyo turn left there.

236
00:13:11,765 --> 00:13:13,364
All right.

237
00:13:13,365 --> 00:13:14,564
It's stopped snowing

238
00:13:14,565 --> 00:13:17,065
so I guess we can get there before 3 am.

239
00:13:20,965 --> 00:13:23,564
But why were you guys in Gunma?

240
00:13:23,565 --> 00:13:25,964
Were you skiing with your grandson?

241
00:13:25,965 --> 00:13:28,064
I guess you could say so.

242
00:13:28,065 --> 00:13:29,465
Sounds great.

243
00:13:37,965 --> 00:13:41,064
Hey. Watch where you're going.

244
00:13:41,065 --> 00:13:42,564
Sorry, sorry.

245
00:13:42,565 --> 00:13:45,565
I shouldn't have driven in the snow after all.

246
00:13:54,065 --> 00:13:55,365
Strange.

247
00:13:56,365 --> 00:13:58,665
There's something fishy about them.

248
00:13:59,665 --> 00:14:00,865
Don't tell me that...

249
00:14:02,065 --> 00:14:04,565
Don't tell me that they're...

250
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:20,339
What's with you anyway?

251
00:14:20,340 --> 00:14:24,139
How many times do you think you got honked at already?

252
00:14:24,140 --> 00:14:28,040
Didn't I tell you that I'm not good at driving on snowy roads?

253
00:14:30,340 --> 00:14:33,439
You're right! This car needs a tune-up

254
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:34,639
and hasn't got its safety check yet,

255
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:36,740
so you've got to drive more carefully!

256
00:14:37,740 --> 00:14:41,339
You're going to get a safety check for this car soon, aren't you?

257
00:14:41,340 --> 00:14:44,640
Yes, I guess so.

258
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:48,039
You don't remember?

259
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:52,640
The number 2 is written on the sticker on the windshield.

260
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:56,839
That's the inspection certificate

261
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:58,339
and depending on the number and the color of the sticker.

