It tells you

263
00:14:59,341 --> 00:15:01,940
when you're supposed to be getting your next safety check, right?

264
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:05,239
The color is this year's color,

265
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:07,239
so it's obvious that you have to get your safety check

266
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:09,139
by February this year.

267
00:15:09,140 --> 00:15:11,439
Oh, that's right. I remember now.

268
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:13,739
Come to think of it, I got a postcard saying

269
00:15:13,740 --> 00:15:15,839
for me to go get my safety check within this month.

270
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:17,839
But, sonny, when did you see it?

271
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:20,339
The sticker was covered with snow.

272
00:15:20,340 --> 00:15:24,939
See. I saw it when the on-coming car passed us.

273
00:15:24,940 --> 00:15:27,139
When the headlights shined on it,

274
00:15:27,140 --> 00:15:29,740
the number outside could be seen transparent from the back.

275
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:39,839
Oh, I see! I thought it was "2"

276
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:43,339
because I saw it transparent from behind but it was actually "5"!

277
00:15:43,340 --> 00:15:44,939
But, that's strange.

278
00:15:44,940 --> 00:15:46,939
You got a postcard saying that you

279
00:15:46,940 --> 00:15:49,539
had to go get a safety check within the month of February, right?

280
00:15:49,540 --> 00:15:51,239
I wonder why?

281
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:54,539
Oh, well, you see... That's...

282
00:15:54,540 --> 00:15:56,939
Didn't I just tell you a while ago,

283
00:15:56,940 --> 00:15:59,339
that he's a Richie Rich, sonny?

284
00:15:59,340 --> 00:16:02,039
That's why he leaves all the details up to others to do it for him.

285
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:03,839
He answered you casually but the thing is,

286
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:06,740
he's not even bothered about the date of the safety check.

287
00:16:08,140 --> 00:16:10,039
You've got to turn right over there,

288
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:12,440
or we won't make it to Tokyo.

289
00:16:16,540 --> 00:16:19,639
Gosh. The kid keeps blabbing on, so...

290
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:23,639
I'm sorry, he's such a curious child.

291
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:26,439
Well, I guess it can't be helped.

292
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:27,840
Okay, there.

293
00:16:33,340 --> 00:16:34,939
By the way,

294
00:16:34,940 --> 00:16:37,139
what are you listening to, sonny?

295
00:16:37,140 --> 00:16:38,639
Oh, this?

296
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:41,339
I'm listening to the news.

297
00:16:41,340 --> 00:16:42,639
News?

298
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:45,639
Yes. There are all kinds of news.

299
00:16:45,640 --> 00:16:51,239
About economy picking up and the new coach of Big Osaka.

300
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:55,039
Or about the jewelry robber who is on the run.

301
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:58,839
You're still so little, yet you like news.

302
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:00,539
Yes.

303
00:17:00,540 --> 00:17:04,639
And? Was the robber caught?

304
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:06,139
No.

305
00:17:06,140 --> 00:17:09,239
They're still escaping somewhere in the Gunma area.

306
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:11,439
But I'm sure they'll be arrested soon.

307
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:12,440
Because... Look.

308
00:17:12,441 --> 00:17:13,839
They seem to have checkpoints here there

309
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:16,040
and everywhere like over there.

310
00:17:25,540 --> 00:17:27,639
License, please.

311
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:28,940
Yes.

312
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:33,339
Excuse me, but where did you come from?

313
00:17:33,340 --> 00:17:35,340
Well...

314
00:17:36,140 --> 00:17:38,040
Officer Yamamura!

315
00:17:38,740 --> 00:17:41,339
You're... you're Conan if I remember correctly.

316
00:17:41,340 --> 00:17:44,139
Officer Yamamura, this is a checkpoint

317
00:17:44,140 --> 00:17:47,639
to arrest the jewelry shop robbers, right?

318
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:49,239
Yes.

319
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:52,939
There are a group of three wearing baseball caps.

320
00:17:52,940 --> 00:17:55,640
After robbing a jewelry shop in Gunma,

321
00:17:56,640 --> 00:18:00,039
they abandoned the car they made their getaway with in the mountains

322
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:02,040
and vanished.

323
00:18:02,940 --> 00:18:06,839
But one of the three is hurt,

324
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:09,839
so I don't think they got too far away yet.

325
00:18:09,840 --> 00:18:11,239
Hurt?

326
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:12,639
Right.

327
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:14,139
When we got the report,

328
00:18:14,140 --> 00:18:18,039
I just happened to be nearby doing some questioning.

329
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:19,139
When I got to the scene of the crime,

330
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:21,239
I happened to run into the robbers

331
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:23,739
who fled out of the shop.

332
00:18:23,740 --> 00:18:27,539
So I pulled out my gun and said,

333
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:31,439
"Freeze. Freeze or I'll shoot".

334
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:33,639
Cool!

335
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:36,539
But the robbers refused to stop

336
00:18:36,540 --> 00:18:38,739
so I fired a warning shot towards them.

337
00:18:38,740 --> 00:18:39,740
Hey.

338
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:45,640
And, I hit one of the robbers in the thigh!

339
00:18:48,140 --> 00:18:49,339
Well, anyway,

340
00:18:49,340 --> 00:18:54,039
either they had another car stashed away in the mountains beforehand,

341
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:56,539
or they stole a car that coincidentally passed through

342
00:18:56,540 --> 00:18:59,139
and are on the run.

343
00:18:59,140 --> 00:19:01,639
Didn't you see some suspicious-looking people?

344
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,639
Yes, I did.

345
00:19:03,640 --> 00:19:06,340
You mean people who are riding in a car that is not theirs, right?

346
00:19:07,940 --> 00:19:10,240
That's us!

347
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:14,639
My car tire went flat in the mountains,

348
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:17,839
so we had them give us a lift.

349
00:19:17,840 --> 00:19:20,539
Right.

350
00:19:20,540 --> 00:19:23,739
Dr. Agasa, where is your car, then?

351
00:19:23,740 --> 00:19:25,739
I called the car dealer

352
00:19:25,740 --> 00:19:27,639
and they said they'd come get it in the morning,

353
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:30,739
so I left it in the mountains with the key inside.

354
00:19:30,740 --> 00:19:33,540
Then, isn't your car in trouble?

355
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:36,639
Maybe the robbers got a hold of it

356
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,639
and are riding it around.

357
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:41,239
That's possible.

358
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:43,539
Then, maybe you shouldn't be bothering with us

359
00:19:43,540 --> 00:19:46,839
and keeping watch over that car.

360
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:50,039
It's a yellow beetle, so it's easy to spot.

361
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:55,139
How strange. Your voices sound familiar.

362
00:19:55,140 --> 00:19:56,339
I don't think so.

363
00:19:56,340 --> 00:19:59,740
So, may we go now, officer?

364
00:20:01,740 --> 00:20:07,239
Will you take that jacket you have over your lap, just in case?

365
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:10,739
Hey! Don't tell me you suspect us?

366
00:20:10,740 --> 00:20:14,139
See, I haven't been shot or anything!

367
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:16,039
I guess not.

368
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:17,840
Be careful, then.

369
00:20:31,140 --> 00:20:33,940
Hello? This is the Agasa residence.

370
00:20:35,540 --> 00:20:37,139
The Gunma Prefectural police?

371
00:20:37,140 --> 00:20:40,939
According to Dr. Agasa, he said that the dealers

372
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:43,439
would be picking his car up in the morning.

373
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:45,939
But, leaving the car as is in the mountains

374
00:20:45,940 --> 00:20:49,439
may give the robbers a chance to use it,

375
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:53,739
so we have decided to tow it away for now.

376
00:20:53,740 --> 00:20:59,539
So, please tell him to come and pick his car up at the station.

377
00:20:59,540 --> 00:21:00,639
Yes, I will.

378
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:02,839
Goodbye, then.

379
00:21:02,840 --> 00:21:04,140
Thank you.

380
00:21:05,740 --> 00:21:09,540
I wonder what they're doing in Gunma at this time of day?

381
00:21:11,140 --> 00:21:13,539
I'll bet he was talked into by Shinichi again

382
00:21:13,540 --> 00:21:16,540
and went sticking their noses into a criminal case or something.

383
00:21:17,740 --> 00:21:19,039
Seriously.

384
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:20,139
I don't see what thrill they find in

385
00:21:20,140 --> 00:21:21,839
looking for faults in others at the cost of losing sleep.

386
00:21:21,840 --> 00:21:24,840
I see no fun at all in playing detective.

387
00:21:34,740 --> 00:21:37,340
A spare pair of pursuit glasses.

388
00:21:48,540 --> 00:21:52,539
Yes, we're going to pick up the stuff earlier than scheduled.

389
00:21:52,540 --> 00:21:55,339
An hour from now, at 4 am.

390
00:21:55,340 --> 00:21:56,939
The place remains unchanged.

391
00:21:56,940 --> 00:22:00,039
It's in front of the locker in the basement of Kenbashi Subway Station.

392
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:02,940
Tell Gin about this too, will you?

393
00:22:04,540 --> 00:22:06,540
Yes, of course.

394
00:22:07,540 --> 00:22:10,739
Get the men ready armed with guns.

395
00:22:10,740 --> 00:22:14,739
He could've gone chicken and called the cops.

396
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:19,239
Either way, after the deal, it's good riddance with him anyway.

397
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:20,639
We were planning to get rid of him

398
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:23,440
inside Kenbashi Station to begin with.

399
00:23:59,140 --> 00:24:02,239
"Next Episode" -It's almost time.

400
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:04,240
Is everyone in position?

401
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:08,340
Don't let one mouse get through.

402
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:14,839
Which means...

403
00:24:14,840 --> 00:24:19,740
Yes. He should still be hiding somewhere nearby.

404
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:25,039
Next Conan,

405
00:24:25,040 --> 00:24:29,140
"Contact with the Black Organization (Desperate Battle Edition)"

